The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also proposes an unsupervised transfer learning method, which involves learning a discriminative representation across domains, and exploiting the underlying commonality across different domains, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of dual classification loss, which is a common technique in multi-modal learning, and hence it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, and hence it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of feature extraction and matching, which are common techniques in information retrieval, and hence it could also belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
